[1] 1st outbreak in Central Mindanao
[2] Control measures

******
[1] 1st outbreak in Central Mindanao
Date: 16 April 2009
Source: BusinessWorld online [edited]
<http://www.bworldonline.com/BW041609/content.php?id=122>


'Panama disease' found in Mindanao banana farm
----------------------------------------------
A devastating disease that targets banana plants has been spotted in
a portion of Central Mindanao region, the regional Department of
Agriculture admitted. Pepito S. Leysa, chief of the Agriculture
department's Regional Crop Protection Center (RCPC), said that
visible manifestations of panama disease, or fusarium wilt, were
discovered in a 3-hectare lakatan banana plantation in Alabel,
Sarangani. Lakatan is a banana variety.

The banana varieties susceptible to panama disease are latundan,
senorita and lakatan. Cavendish banana has succumbed to the new
strain (race 4) of the disease. Saba or cardaba, on the other hand,
is a resistant cultivar, the statement added.

Panama disease was 1st reported in the Philippines in 1920 on
latundan variety in Los Banos and Calamba, Laguna, and in
municipalities of Batangas. It was confirmed in commercial Cavendish
farms in 1974 and 1979. The pathogen ended up totally destroying 13
hectares of latundan farms in Eden, Toril in Davao City.

Aside from panama disease, the affected banana farm was also infested
by the banana bunchy top virus, moko and sigatoka diseases, Mr. Leysa
said. It was the 1st time that crop protection experts confirmed the
presence of the devastating panama disease in Central Mindanao
region. The region hosts at least 3 large banana producers.

[Byline: Romer S. Sarmiento]

